# Nimara — Cursor rules

**Single source of truth:** read [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) and the skills under
[`.agents/skills/`](../../.agents/skills/). This file is a thin pointer so guidance stays
in one place — do not duplicate rules here.

## Stack (quick orientation)

Next.js 16 (App Router, RSC, Server Actions) · React 19 · TypeScript strict · Tailwind +
Shadcn UI · Saleor GraphQL (codegen) · Turborepo + pnpm · NextAuth v5 · Stripe · Vitest +
Playwright.

## Structure (authoritative list)

```
apps/        storefront · marketplace · stripe · docs · automated-tests
packages/    domain · foundation · infrastructure · features · ui · config · codegen · i18n · eslint-config-custom
```

- `domain` & `foundation` are leaf packages.
- `infrastructure` depends on `domain` + `foundation` only.
- `features` composes all packages; apps depend on features/infrastructure/ui/foundation/domain/config.

## The rules that matter most

- Server Components first; `"use client"` only for interactivity/hooks/browser APIs.
- Wrap fallible operations in `Result<T, E>` from `@nimara/domain/objects/Result`.
- Run `pnpm codegen` after `.graphql` changes; never hand-write generated GraphQL types.
- Named exports only (Next route/page/layout files exempt).
- Never import `@nimara/codegen` from app/component code — go through services.
- NEVER add a dependency automatically — ask first.

For everything else (layers decision tree, React/Next patterns, composition, a11y), see
the matching skill in `.agents/skills/`.
